---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Hot Water Cranbourne | Gas, Heat-Pump, Solar, Same-Day Repairs | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Hot water specialists in Cranbourne — same-day repairs, gas / heat-pump / solar / electric replacements. Cranbourne, Cranbourne East, Cranbourne West, Cranbourne North, Lyndhurst, Clyde. Solar Vic rebate. VBA-licensed."
  canonical="https://sehotwater.com.au/cranbourne/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Cranbourne &middot; Cranbourne East / West / North &middot; Lyndhurst &middot; Clyde</span>
      <h1>Hot water in <span class="accent">Cranbourne</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Cranbourne is two suburbs in one: the original 1970s&ndash;90s township
        running tired old gas storage tanks, and the booming new estates of
        Cranbourne East and Cranbourne North on gas instantaneous. We handle
        both. Same-day repairs, full replacements, and the $1,000 Solar Vic
        rebate handled in-house.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Cranbourne</span>
      <h2>The Cranbourne hot water story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Old Cranbourne &mdash; the 1970s-80s gas storage population.</h3>
        <p>
          The original Cranbourne residential streets around the train station,
          South Gippsland Highway, Camms Road and Berwick-Cranbourne Road are
          full of 1970s&ndash;80s brick-veneer homes with externally-mounted
          Rheem Stellar, Vulcan, or Bosch internal storage tanks. A solid
          chunk of these units are 20&ndash;30+ years old &mdash; double their
          design life. The cylinders are corroding from the inside. We
          replace 3&ndash;4 a week in old Cranbourne alone.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">New Cranbourne East / North &mdash; mid-2000s instantaneous now ageing.</h3>
        <p>
          Cranbourne East (Hunt Club, Botanic Ridge), Cranbourne North (Carrum
          Downs side), and Clyde all grew rapidly from 2003 onwards with
          Rinnai Infinity 24/26 and Bosch Highflow 21 instantaneous units
          mounted on the side wall. The earliest of these are now 18+ years
          old and the electronic ignition boards are reaching end-of-life.
          We service the boards in-place where possible, replace the unit
          where the heat exchanger has scaled up.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Heat-pump conversion &mdash; the big rebate winner.</h3>
        <p>
          Cranbourne is the Solar Vic rebate sweet-spot &mdash; large 4-bedroom
          family homes, big hot-water demand, owner-occupiers under the income
          cap. Converting from gas storage or 1990s gas instantaneous to a
          280&ndash;315L heat-pump nets you the $1,000 Solar Vic rebate plus
          ~$1,000 in STCs, dropping the install to $3K&ndash;$4.5K. Running cost
          savings ~$500&ndash;$700/year vs gas. Payback in 5&ndash;6 years on
          conversion premium.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Cranbourne jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>20-year-old Rheem Stellar 250L gas storage replacement &mdash; like-for-like Rinnai HotFlo 250L ($2.1K&ndash;$2.5K)</li>
          <li>Gas instantaneous to heat-pump conversion (Reclaim 280L) &mdash; $3.5K&ndash;$4K net after rebates</li>
          <li>Solar hot water tank replacement (existing panels stay) &mdash; $2.5K&ndash;$3.5K</li>
          <li>Same-day no-hot-water repair &mdash; $200&ndash;$500 most calls</li>
          <li>Electric storage to heat-pump (rebate-eligible owner-occupiers) &mdash; $3K&ndash;$4K net</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other South East service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/berwick/">Berwick</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/endeavour-hills/">Endeavour Hills</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/south-east-melbourne/">All South East Melbourne</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Cranbourne hot water quote.</h2>
        <p>Heat-pump vs gas honest comparison. Solar Vic rebate done in-house.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
